Interface for manage the Earth Engine Asset

Source: R/ee_manage.R
ee_manage-tools.Rd

R functions for managing the Earth Engine Asset

ee_manage_create(path_asset, asset_type = "folder", quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_delete(path_asset, quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_assetlist(path_asset, quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_quota()

ee_manage_size(path_asset)

ee_manage_copy(path_asset, final_path, quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_move(path_asset, final_path, quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_set_properties(path_asset, properties)

ee_manage_delete_properties(path_asset, property)

ee_manage_assets_access(path_asset,
  acl = getOption("rgee.manage.getAssetAcl"), quiet = FALSE)

ee_manage_task(quiet, cache = TRUE)

ee_manage_cancel_all_running_taks()

Arguments

path_asset

Character. Name of the EE asset e.g. users/user/nameofcollection.
asset_type

Character. The asset type ('folder' or 'imagecollection').
quiet

Logical. Suppress info message.
final_path

Character. Name of the final EE asset to copy or move.
properties

List. Set of parameters to established as a property of an EE object. See details.
property

Character. Name of a specific property to be deleted.
acl

A list describing the asset's Access Control List. See getOption("rgee.manage.getAssetAcl").
cache

Logical. TRUE save the report in the /temp directory.

Examples

library(rgee)
# Change the user and google account to be able to reproduce
ee_Initialize(user_gmail = 'csaybar@gmail.com')
#> Requesting Earth Engine authorization  ... DONE
ee_manage_create('users/csaybar/rgee')
#> GEE asset: users/csaybar/rgee created

# 1. List all the elements inside a folder or a ImageCollection
ee_manage_assetlist(path_asset = 'users/csaybar/rgee')
#> data frame with 0 columns and 0 rows

# 2. Create a Folder or a ImageCollection
ee_manage_create('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder',asset_type = 'folder')
#> GEE asset: users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder created
ee_manage_create('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_ic',asset_type = 'imagecollection')
#> GEE asset: users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_ic created
ee_manage_assetlist('users/csaybar/rgee')
#>                               ID            TYPE
#> 2     users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_ic ImageCollection
#> 1 users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder          Folder

# 3. Shows your Earth Engine quota
ee_manage_quota()
#>  Total Quota: 250.00 GB 
#>  Used Quota: 778.14 MB

# 4. Estimate the size of a Image, ImageCollection, Table or Folder.
ee_manage_size('users/csaybar/rgee')
#> Folder :
#>  - Size: 0 B
#>  - # elements: 2

# 5. Move a EE object to another folder
ee_manage_move(path_asset = 'users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_ic',
               final_path = 'users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved')
#> Done
ee_manage_assetlist('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder')
#>                                             ID            TYPE
#> 1 users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved ImageCollection

# 6. Set properties to an EE object.
ee_manage_set_properties(path_asset = 'users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved',
                         properties = list(message='hello-world',language = 'R'))
test_ic <- ee$ImageCollection('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved')
test_ic$getInfo()
#> $features
#> list()
#> 
#> $id
#> [1] "users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved"
#> 
#> $properties
#> $properties$language
#> [1] "R"
#> 
#> $properties$message
#> [1] "hello-world"
#> 
#> 
#> $version
#> [1] 1878938063
#> 
#> $type
#> [1] "ImageCollection"
#> 
#> $bands
#> list()
#> 

# 7. Delete properties
ee_manage_delete_properties(path_asset = 'users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved',
                            property = c("message","language"))
test_ic$getInfo()
#> $id
#> [1] "users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved"
#> 
#> $version
#> [1] 1880803599
#> 
#> $features
#> list()
#> 
#> $type
#> [1] "ImageCollection"
#> 
#> $bands
#> list()
#> 

# 8. Share EE objects -- Create a public dataset
ee_manage_assets_access('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved')
#> The ACL of users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved has been changed.
ee$data$getAssetAcl('users/csaybar/rgee/rgee_folder/rgee_ic_moved')
#> $owners
#> [1] "csaybar@gmail.com"
#> 
#> $readers
#> [1] "csaybar@gmail.com"
#> 
#> $all_users_can_read
#> [1] TRUE
#> 
#> $writers
#> [1] "csaybar@gmail.com"
#>
